# Variable naming

Use **full-word**, intention-revealing names for variables, parameters, destructuring, catches, and callbacks (`item`, `event`, `error`). Avoid meaningless single letters (`x`, `e`, `n`, `k`, `v`, …) unless below.

## Exceptions

- **`t`** — i18n translate only (`useTranslation`, `getServerT`). Not for arbitrary strings or data.
- **`i`**, **`j`** — loop counters / numeric **index** args in `map` / `filter` / `forEach` when the meaning is “position”; inner loop uses **`j`** when outer is **`i`**. Not for ids, events, or domain values.
- **API-mandated** short names — allowed; alias to a clearer local when it helps.
- **Math / geometry** — **`x`**, **`y`**, etc. only in small numeric helpers where standard; document if odd.

```typescript
const itemCount = items.length;
items.map((item) => transform(item));
function onClick(event: MouseEvent) {
  event.preventDefault();
}
const { t } = useTranslation();
items.map((item, i) => transform(item, i));
```

**New and edited** code. Prefer **`catch (error)`** over **`err`** unless matching external docs.
